24/06/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Serbian President Boris Tadic, in Zagreb for the regional energy summit, issued an apology Saturday (June 23rd) to the Croatian people for war-related hardships. "I apologise to all members of the Croatian nation who have been made unhappy, and on behalf of my people, I am taking responsibility for that," Tadic said during an interview with the Nedjeljom u Dva talk show on Croatian state TV. According to the station, Tadic is the first senior official from Belgrade to extend such an apology. (HRT, Beta - 23/06/07)
